ty of south carolina; columbia, sc"], "date": "1924-01-23", "dates": ["1924-01-23"], "description": ["1 7 MOSfOll SAMARIA The following pupils made the hon or roll of Samaria school tor the month of December First GradeKdna Gregory Myrtle Hall Advanced FirstHarney Gregory Annie Gillian Seoonc GradeRuth Hall Minnie Gillian Third GradeGeorge Kirkland Fourth GradeJesse Gilian Fifth GradeJames Kirkland Ode Hall Tmagene Hall Sixth GradeHenry Hall Seventh GradeR E Gregory Jr Tenth GradeIva Davis ST STEPHENS CHURCH Sunday school at 10 a m B H Barre superintendent Divine services Ay 4 Off Summer Pastures i Your animals are coming off summer pastures 5 and going on dry feed Its a big change Out in tlje succulent pastures Nature supplies the tonics aiid laxatives to keep animals in condition r fBut unless you supply these tonics and laxa tives to your stock on dry feed you are not going to get full returns from your hay grain and fodder Besides your animals are apt to get off feed and out of fix rir n v i I W V v Hess Stock Tonic Supplies the TonicsLaxativesDiuretics i H vi It keeps animals free from worm It keeps their bowels open and regular It keeps the appefite and digestion good It conditions cows for calving It helps"], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2025-04-13T07:34:54.484Z", "group": ["ndnp/scu", "university-of-south-carolina-columbia-sc-awardee"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/resource/sn86063761/1924-01-23/ed-1/?sp=8", "image_url": ["https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:scu:batch_scu_figs_ver02:data:sn86063761:00516990831:1924012301:0270/full/pct:3.125/0/default.jpg#h=257&w=174", "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:scu:batch_scu_figs_ver02:data:sn86063761:00516990831:1924012301:0270/full/pct:6.25/0/default.jpg#h=515&w=349", "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:scu:batch_scu_figs_ver02:data:sn86063761:00516990831:1924012301:0270/full/pct:12.5/0/default.jpg#h=1030&w=698", "https://tile.l